[{"id":"VR786355","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three identical conducting spheres on insulating stands. Sphere A has a charge of positive 1 microcoulomb, Sphere B has a charge of positive 5 microcoulombs, and Sphere C has a charge of positive 3 microcoulombs. A note indicates that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR786355.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three identical conducting spheres with different initial amounts of charge are on insulating stands, as shown in the figure. The spheres are far enough apart that they have no effect on each otherâ€™s charge. At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub 0\"><math alttext=\"t sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>, the net charge on each sphere is as indicated in the figure. At a later time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub 1\"><math alttext=\"t sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> have been briefly brought into contact and then returned to their initial positions. At a still later time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub 2\"><math alttext=\"t sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> have been briefly brought into contact and then returned to their initial positions. Which of the following correctly ranks the magnitude of the charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span> on Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> at the three different times?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR786355_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 0 is greater than Q sub 1, which equals Q sub 2\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 0 is greater than Q sub 1, which equals Q sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 0 is greater than Q sub 2, which is greater than Q sub 1\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 0 is greater than Q sub 2, which is greater than Q sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1 is greater than Q sub 0, which is greater than Q sub 2\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1 is greater than Q sub 0, which is greater than Q sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_p